news.title: CAG flags various issues in Nagpur metro project, says MMRCL could not monetize land parcels
news.para: In the report, the CAG observed, as per the detailed project report, the commercial operation of phase 1 was to be achieved by April 2018 but only two out of four Reaches have begun commercial operation.

news.title: Hefty fees keep property owners away from Gunthewari scheme in Pune
news.para: According to the Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC)'s data, residents seeking regularisation of unauthorised properties would have to pay three times the ready reckoner rates for getting the proposal approved.

news.title: Coimbatore corporation asks residents to link ration card details with property tax number
news.para: Commercial building owners have been asked to link their PAN card details or GST number with the property tax number.

news.title: Real estate sector grows apace in current financial year in Jaipur
news.para: Sharad Mehra, inspector general, registration & stamps, said, “The real estate sector has witnessed strong growth, reflecting the increase in revenue collections. If the trend continues, which is likely, the department will reach near the target set for the current financial year.”

news.title: Home registration in Kolkata up 167% year-on-year in November 2022
news.para: Since the initial stamp duty cut announcement in July 2021, a whopping 72,790 residential properties have been registered in the city in these 17 months. The preceding 17 months prior to the introduction of rebate saw registration of only 44,736 units.

news.title: Adani Group offers to relocate employees after cement plants' closure
news.para: The statement stated that 85 employees of Darlaghat plant in Solan and 58 from Barmana plant in Bilaspur would be relocated to nearby sister plants of Adani group.

news.title: Kochi: Assets of Holy Faith H2O builders to be auctioned
news.para: Holy faith H20 was the first building razed on January 11, 2020. The auction will be held on January 20 next year to realize Rs 42 crore.

news.title: North Goa collector directs Canara Bank to sell off builder's assets
news.para: The collector has asked Canara Bank to recover Rs 4 crore as the money owed to the creditors along with an interest penalty of Rs 50 lakh.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC to buy out AAI's Dahisar land for Rs 473 crore
news.para: Municipal commissioner and administrator I S Chahal said the height restrictions on account of the high transmission towers at Dahisar will go allowing buildings to go up to 25 metres and make them financially viable.

news.title: Soon, a colony of affordable houses in Gurugram sector 9
news.para: The proposed houses will be allotted to below poverty line (BPL) families and beneficiaries will be identified through Parivar Pehchan Patra (PPP), housing board officials said.

news.title: Home First Finance raises Rs 280 crore from IFC
news.para: The proceeds will be utilized to provide financing for retail buyers of affordable housing and green affordable housing units, encouraging home ownership for low-income segments, and supporting the development of green affordable housing.

news.title: Credit Suisse sells building in Geneva for $217 million
news.para: The Swiss bank, which is trying to recover from a string of scandals, is set to remain a long-term tenant of the building.

news.title: Puravankara & Purva Real Estate Fund acquires more than 100 acres of land in Chennai
news.para: “Puravankara and the AIF fund partly acquired the land. The biggest strength of plotted projects is clarity on the title and government-approved developments,” said Abhishek Kapoor, CEO, Puravankara.

news.title: HDFC gets $400 million IFC loan for financing green affordable housing units
news.para: HDFC said it has earmarked 75 per cent or USD 300 million of the IFC funding for financing green affordable housing units.

news.title: Maharashtra finally notifies changed regularisation rules for Ulhasnagar buildings
news.para: The state amended rules under the Regularisation of Unauthorised Development in the City of Ulhasnagar Act, 2006, which now stipulates lower fines to regularize such buildings.
